Key Match Events: Ben Stokes scored an unbeaten 107 off 109 balls
Post-Match Reflections: Ben Stokes expressed his satisfaction with the victory
Jos Buttler acknowledged the team's desperation for the win
Scott Edwards admitted that Netherlands did not start well with the ball and could have tried different plans with the bat
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was the penultimate game for both England and Netherlands in the ODI World Cup 2023
Others: England relied heavily on Chris Woakes to restrict Australia to 286 in their previous match
Netherlands suffered a seven-wicket defeat over Afghanistan in their most recent game
